# No Code Comments

Do not add comments to code. Write clear, self-explanatory code (descriptive names, small functions) instead of explaining it with comments.

This applies to all comment forms:
- Line comments (`//`)
- Block comments (`/* */`)
- JSDoc/doc comments (`/** */`)
- JSX comments (`{/* */}`)

```tsx
// BAD
// build the playable list
const segments = useMemo(() => { ... }, []);

{/* Prev */}
<button onClick={onPrev} />

// GOOD
const segments = useMemo(() => { ... }, []);

<button aria-label="Previous" onClick={onPrev} />
```

Exception: only keep a comment when explicitly requested by the user, or when it conveys a legally required notice (e.g. a license header).
